accessibility.text: P4: maybe that's the way you're supposed to, [] you can pick and choose what you want, in your mind, what is your vision of the character.

P5: they had the wrong voices and i just couldn't watch it because they weren't nagging...terrible voices that are not the real authentic one [] he hadn't that voice anymore, so it was not a real Scrooge McDuck. it was a fake one.
P7: the costume as well you know that that provides a link, if you like, between all these different representations it's unacceptable [for Tinker Bell to wear a different outfit] (laughs).
